<img width="107" height="107" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/Allen-Onyema1-107x107.jpg?resize=107%2C107&amp;ssl=1" alt="Lawyer tells court to stop extradition of Air Peace boss, Onyema, to US" class="amp-wp-295b586"> A human rights lawyer, Johnmary Jideobi, has urged the Federal High Court, Abuja, to restrain the Federal Government from extraditing the Chairman, Air Peace Airline Company, Allen Onyema, to the United States (US) for trial in an alleged fraud. Jideobi, in a suit with reference no: FHC/ABJ/CS/1446/2019 filed, on Nov. 25, also sought the court order barring government, its agencies, servants of privies from giving effect to any extradition request from any country of the world, especially the US, anchored on any indictment or charges reflecting in substance or similar fact as contained in the US extradition request against Onyema. Continue reading Lawyer tells court to stop extradition of Air Peace boss, Onyema, to US at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard